{"id":24963,"date":"2017-06-05T13:57:23","date_gmt":"2017-06-05T09:57:23","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=24963"},"modified":"2022-08-01T09:56:24","modified_gmt":"2022-08-01T05:56:24","slug":"dua-affirm-hearts-deen","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/06\/05\/dua-affirm-hearts-deen\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Guidance: O Allah, affirm our hearts upon Your religion"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Umm Salamah reported: \u00a0I said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, how often you supplicate saying: <strong>O Turner of the hearts, keep my heart firm upon Your religion.<\/strong>\u201d The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>O Umm Salamah, there is no human but that his heart is between the fingers of Allah. Whoever He wills is made steadfast and whoever He wills is deviated<\/strong>.\u201d Mu&#8217;adh recited the verse, &#8220;<strong>Our Lord, do not let our hearts deviate after you have guided us<\/strong>.&#8221; (3:8)<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 3522<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u0646 \u0623\u0645 \u0633\u0644\u0645\u0629 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u062a\u0652 \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064f\u0644\u0652\u062a\u064f \u064a\u064e\u0627 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u0643\u0652\u062b\u064e\u0631\u064e \u062f\u064f\u0639\u064e\u0627\u0621\u064e\u0643\u064e <strong>\u064a\u064e\u0627 \u0645\u064f\u0642\u064e\u0644\u0651\u0650\u0628\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0642\u064f\u0644\u064f\u0648\u0628\u0650 \u062b\u064e\u0628\u0651\u0650\u062a\u0652 \u0642\u064e\u0644\u0652\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u062f\u0650\u064a\u0646\u0650\u0643\u064e<\/strong> \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0